<chapter xml:id="ch-chapter-title" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Kepler's Laws of Planetary Motion</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> Johannas Kepler observed the sky for many - many years in early <m>17^{th}</m> century and gave the following three major laws.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          <term>The law of orbit:</term> In Solar system, every planet revolves in an elliptical orbit having <term>Sun</term> at one of its focii.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <term>The law of area:</term> Planet sweeps out an equal area in equal interval of time in the orbit.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <term>The law of period:</term> The square of time period of planet around the sun is directly proportional to the cube of semi-major axis.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    
  </introduction>

